{
  "texts": [
    "Related WorkThe landscape of Natural Language Understanding (NLU) has witnessed a prolific evolution, propelled by the relentless pursuit of enhanced natural language processing capabilities.",
    "In this section, we review and contextualize our study within the broader literature, focusing on the advancements in both encoder-only and decoderonly models and how they are applied for intent classification and sentiment analysis tasks.Intent classification and sentiment analysis have been extensively studied in the field of NLP, with numerous approaches proposed over the years.",
    "Traditional methods often relied on hand-crafted features, such as n-grams and sentiment lexicons, to extract relevant information from text.",
    "Due to the very large dimension of the input space, classifiers such as Adaboost [9] and SVM [10] were found effective.",
    "However, these methods were limited by their reliance on manual feature engineering and their inability to capture complex contextual relationships.The advent of deep learning revolutionized the landscape of intent classification and sentiment analysis."
  ]
}